  "prompt": "When will I start the preparation of ilts?",
  "response": "It seems like you're asking about preparing for the IELTS (International English Language Testing System) exam. To help you plan effectively, here are some steps to consider:\n\n### Determine Your Target Score and Test Date\n1. **Identify your target score**: Depending on the institution or organization you're applying to, you'll need to achieve a certain band score.\n2. **Choose a test date**: Look at the available test dates and choose one that aligns with your application deadlines.\n\n### Assess Your Current Level\n- **Take a practice test**: This will give you a baseline of your current English proficiency and help you identify areas for improvement.\n\n### Plan Your Preparation Timeline\n- **If you have 3-6 months**:\n  - **Months 1-2**: Focus on building your foundational skills in listening, reading, writing, and speaking. Use textbooks, online resources, and language learning apps.\n  - **Months 3-4**: Begin taking full-length practice tests to simulate the exam experience. Analyze your performance to identify weaknesses.\n  - **Months 5-6**: Concentrate on refining your skills, especially in areas where you need improvement. Continue taking practice tests to track your progress.\n\n- **If you have 1-2 months**:\n  - **Weeks 1-4**: Start with intensive study sessions focusing on all four sections of the exam. Use practice tests to gauge your progress and adjust your study plan accordingly.\n  - **Weeks 5-8**: Continue practicing and refining your skills. Take at least one full-length practice test per week.\n\n### Additional Tips\n- **Daily practice**: Consistency is key. Allocate time each day to practice different sections of the exam.\n- **Seek feedback**: If possible, get feedback from a tutor or language partner, especially for the speaking and writing sections.\n- **Use official resources**: The IELTS website offers valuable resources, including sample questions and practice tests.\n\n### Final Weeks Before the Exam\n- **Last 2 weeks**: Focus on reviewing and taking more practice tests. Avoid learning new material and concentrate on reinforcing what you already know.\n- **Exam day preparation**: Ensure you have all necessary documents, get a good night's sleep, and arrive early at the test center.\n\nBy following these steps, you'll be well-prepared for the IELTS exam. Good luck with your preparation!",
